Basic operations in files and folers:

1. DIR (To Open list of files & Folders in Current Location)

2. MKDIR (To Create Folder)

3. REN (To Rename Files & Folders)

4. DEL (To Delete Files)

5. COPY (To Copy Files & Folders)

6. MOVE (To Move Files & Folders)

7. RMDIR (To Delete Folders)

8. CD (To Change Directory)

9. CD/ (To Return Drive Location Out of all Folders)

10. CD.. (To Return a step Backward)
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
*to enter to any directory use "cd  <nameofdirectory>"            [cd= current directory]
C:\Users\asus>cd desktop

*to come out of directory use "cd.."
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>cd..

*to come out of all directories use "cd/"
C:\Users\asus>cd/
C:\>cd 

*to make a folder(directory) use "mkdir  <nameoffolder>"
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>mkdir hello

* to rename a folder use "ren <oldname> <newname>"
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>ren hello world

* to create a file use "type nul> <nameoffile>"
C:\Users\asus\Desktop\world>type nul> first.txt

*to copy a file from desktop to any folder use " copy <filetobecopied> <locaton>"
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>copy questions.txt world
        1 file(s) copied.
        
*to move a file from desktop to any folder use " copy <filetobecopied> <locaton>"        
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>move first.txt world
        1 file(s) moved.

* to delete the folder use" rmdir <foldername>"
C:\Users\asus\Desktop>rmdir world

